&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Nurse in Sexual Health - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Wolverton is a well-established Contraception, Sexual Health and HIV service based at Kingston Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clients contacting the service have access to virtual and telephone appointments for all aspects of care, medication collection services including PrEP and booked appointments as indicated by the client&#39;s need. Specialist services run by The Wolverton include routine and complex contraception, The Connect service for clients with learning disabilities, a psychology service and inclusion within a Trust wide vulval pain management model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Wolverton has adapted during the COVID - 19 pandemic and has maintained a core service throughout whilst now incorporating service innovations, initiated in response to the pandemic, into the routine service where this holds benefit for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 6 nurses within the service are central to the smooth running and excellent client care that we offer. As well as directly working with clients during consultations the senior nursing team oversea the results and partner notification process, provide leadership and management to junior technician and nursing staff as well providing the core staff for contraception and Implant requesting clients. While previous sexual health experience may be beneficial we welcome applicants from other nursing roles with appropriate transferable skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you could work well within our team alongside dedicated colleagues please contact Judith Murray for more information judithmurray2@nhs.net or apply direct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Judith Murray [Interim Lead Nurse] - judithmurray2@nhs.net - 020 8974 9331&lt;/p&gt;
